features: Sets up in under 5 minutes (based on average setup time with 2 people) thanks to preattached poles
LED lighting provides warm, diffused overhead light, powered by 3 AA batteries (sold separately)
Extended interior space​ fits 3 queen airbeds; includes a room divider and 2 doors (front and back)
Nearly vertical walls provide more headroom

WeatherTec system uses a tub-like floor and patented welded corners, while inverted seams and taped seams on rainfly and tent body help keep water out; durable frame is tested to withstand winds up to 35 mph
2 wide doors (front and back) make it easier to move airbeds, sleeping bags, and other gear in and out of the tent
Large door awnings provide more weather protection and better airflow
E-port makes it easy to access an extension cord so you can bring electrical power inside your tent
Mesh storage pockets keep gear organized
Rainfly connections to left of doors, and brow pole sleeves are color-coded red to help with orientation
Expandable carry bag for easy packing
